  "texts": [
    "Active Learning (AL) is a novel introduction to the field of de Novo Drug Design for the exploration of chemical space.",
    "AL operates on the principle that models can achieve higher accuracy with fewer data by intelligently selecting their training samples.",
    "Central to AL is the concept of uncertainty.",
    "AL addresses epistemic uncertainty, related to the lack of knowledge in certain areas of the modeled space by the model (88).",
    "For instance, an unfamiliar molecular structure can increase uncertainty in predictions due to insufficient knowledge in that area."
